VBCCs startup code calls main(), if you're creating a library you should
link without startup code -- but you'll then need to supply a ROM tag,
jump table etc. which is automatically created by StormC, but has to be
manually done with VBCC (AFAIK), I'm sure you can find examples of this
on Aminet, but if you only want to test the quality of VBCC then I'd
start by simply compiling your code into an executable, and if it turns
out to be faster, start working on making your own library out of it.

