algorithm.  Another method that just came to mind was this:

int index, r, src[MY_MAX_SIZE], array_size = MY_MAX_SIZE, res[MY_MAX_SIZE]

0 fill(src) 				// put in numbers to be shuffled
1 index = 0
2 choose r = rand( 0, array_size )	// get a random element
3 res[index] = src[r]			// copy the value				
4 src[r] = src[array_size-1]		// copy the last value to the hole
5 index++, array_size--
6 if( array_size > 0 ) goto 2 else return // keep going till no more

Rather than copy the array down, just adjust it.  (Idea borrowed from heap
sort I suppose)

It certainly isn't an ideal approach, but it's just a though :)

