Subject: @{b}Re: CreateTask@{ub}

On 23-Oct-00, René wrote:
> Hi!
> Here is a Problem. I create a new task with CreateTask. The code is a
> simple scrolltext. see example. After finish this example my mashine
> hangs :( Can any user help me?

> thanks & bye...


void task(void)
{
 int x;
 while(1)
 {
  x=100;
  while(x>-100)
  {
   PrintIText(win->RPort,&itxt,x,0);
   WaitTOF();
   x--;
  }
 }
}

Ooow, nasty......

Who's  "RPort" or  "win"  & "itxt"   are you refering to  ??
Also,  the variable "win"  even if it is global,  may not be valid
for these reasons...

1:   The parent process has exited....
      Resulting in an invalid pointer  (you don't check it)
      AND,  if it has exited,  your task is now running
      in freed memory....

2:   You may be referencing data in a "small code"  model
      requiring register A4 to point to the data segment & data
      is referenced via an offset of register A4...
     With no A4 set properly, the data reference could be anywhere..

3:   The  "&itxt"  itself is in the same boat,  it may not be
      referencing it properly...
       

Another nasty......
Your task can never exit,  and it must do so BEFORE the
spawning process exits as it's code has been LoadSeg'ed()
by dos & UnLoadSeg'ed() when your main process leaves.

