In addition to what Colin said:

The  best way IMO, to handle sub tasks is to AllocSignal() in the main task
and  use  that  signal  in the sub task to notify the main task when it has
finished.   Once  the  signal  has been sent the main task can be sure it's
safe  to  DeleteTask().   It  is  also  very important to stop the sub task
idefinately  while  it's  waiting to be deleted - use Wait(NULL) - lest the
sub task begins to execute illegal machine code.  Another method is for the
sub task to delete itself.


Regards

Steve


