  Thats true, symbol information are not stripped by default. Adding "-s"
  during linking removes them.
  However, compiling with -O3 will probably result in bigger code since
  GCC turns "auto-inlining" on at this level. However, using higher
  optimizations levels than -O2 should be avoided since at least 2.95[.2]
  is unreliable [read: broken] at this level.

