On Sat, 28 Oct 2000, Jack York wrote:

> On the StormC list I posted a question about why a call to the 
> function OnMenu wouldn't work with StormC.  I was told to
> "use the stubs of the amiga.lib and not the '#pragma amicall."
> So, instead of just a direct call to a function I create another
> function that I call and that calls OnMenu.  I am just curious
> as to why this is so. [...]

As you can see from my contribution to that discussion, it is possible
to call the library function directly.

The difference between a stub and a library function is that the later
expects arguments in registers, and a library pointer in A6. The stubs
found in amiga.lib expects parameters on the stack (which is standard C
calling convention( and doesn't expect to receive the library base.

Hope that helps...

Regards Allan


