Well, you are. C doesn't know anything about strings, they are just arrays
of chars. By doing what you did, you compared the address at which the array
myname is stored to the address where the "Francis" constant is stored in
the program. Of course they aren't equal. To compare two strings you should
use the strcmp() function which is declared in string.h:

#include <string.h>

//...

if (strcmp(myname, "Francis") == 0)

> BTW, I'm using StormC 3.0.

It shouldn't matter. It's a pure ANSI C thing.

